cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.IR 

The paper discusses computer vision techniques for remote sensing images, specifically aerial images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the development of a novel approach for open set semantic segmentation, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of drones and imaging satellites also suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) could be a relevant category. Finally, the paper discusses the availability of public datasets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
